<title type="html"><![CDATA[Win7 Username = user does not work]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=603&amp;p=3063#p3063"><![CDATA[
I am creating this item because I have not been able to find relevant entries using the Forum Search. <br />I have several machines using classicshell 3.6.6. On two of the machines ClassicShell doesn't seem to work correctly (Search doesn't affect the Recent Programs, etc.). I have not pursued it in Classic Explorer, etc. The only common factor that I can see is that the way that Win7 was installed causes a default Username of &quot;user&quot; instead of the Username of the logon (sometimes documented as &lt;user&gt;). <br /><br />How can I configure Classic Shell to handle this problem? <br /><br />Or, better yet:<br />Can I &quot;fix&quot; Win7 to display the logged on Username? It would solve other issues, too. <br /><br />Jim Nelson<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=677">jnelson5806</a> — Mon Apr 29, 2013 8:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
